In this press briefing, President Trump discusses various topics including healthcare, tax reform, the controversy surrounding Tom Price's use of private planes, his confidence in Mitch McConnell, and the NFL protests. He mentions that they have the votes for healthcare but can't proceed due to a senator being in the hospital. He also mentions plans to negotiate with Democrats for a bipartisan healthcare bill. Regarding tax reform, he states that the 20% corporate rate is a red line for him. He addresses the issue of Puerto Rico's recovery efforts and the possibility of lifting the Jones Act. He also comments on the travel ban and the controversy surrounding the NFL protests, expressing his belief that the NFL needs to change its stance on players kneeling during the national anthem. Finally, he discusses his dissatisfaction with Tom Price's use of private planes and his consideration of whether to fire him.